{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"Branch staleness detection correctly identifies branches with commits not in main, older than the configured age threshold, and no open PR.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure is primarily at local module handoffs: commit-diff computation, age-threshold evaluation, and PR-presence signal combined into one decision. This is more than a single pure function, but does not inherently require real network/subprocess if git/PR inputs are provided through local adapters.","test_description":"Wire the real staleness evaluator with a fixture branch-state provider and PR-state provider. Use table-driven cases including: ahead+old+no PR => stale, ahead+fresh+no PR => not stale, not ahead+old+no PR => not stale. Assert exact decision and boundary behavior at the configured age cutoff.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.23,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Session-start setup emits a stale-work warning with actionable branch context when the current branch is stale.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The risk is bootstrap wiring: detector output must flow into session-start messaging with correct branch context. A unit test of formatter alone would miss this integration handoff.","test_description":"Run session-start initialization with a stubbed current-branch context and real warning-emission path. Feed a stale classification and assert one emitted warning includes branch name, age/commit context, and clear next action (open PR). Also assert no warning for clean classification in the same harness.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"A local status-classifier function maps computed branch state to labels (`clean`, `stale-no-pr`) deterministically.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This behavior is explicitly a local deterministic mapping function with no I/O or external boundary.","test_description":"Pure function tests over exhaustive state combinations relevant to the label domain. Assert exact label outputs and repeat-call determinism for identical inputs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.93,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.005,"Workflow":0.005}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"`/kaizen-wip` against live repo and PR state distinguishes \"clean\" from \"has commits but no PR (STALE)\" in rendered output.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"The behavior explicitly depends on live repository and live PR state, crossing subprocess/OS and external API boundaries. Mocking can hide real contract and state-sync failures.","test_description":"In a real test repo and real PR backend, execute `/kaizen-wip` end-to-end for two scenarios: branch synced with main, and branch ahead with no PR and older than threshold. Assert rendered status text matches expected labels and stale wording exactly.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.09,"System":0.88,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"Branches with open or merged PRs are not flagged as stale-no-PR false positives.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Correctness depends on real PR lifecycle states (open/merged) as returned by the actual provider and interpreted by the detector. Mock-only tests can miss real-state mapping differences.","test_description":"Create/identify branches with (a) open PR and (b) merged PR, then run stale detection via the production PR-state path. Assert both are never labeled `stale-no-pr`, even when branch age and prior ahead status would otherwise qualify.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.22,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Staleness detection remains correct across rebases or squash merges where commit hashes change but branch state should no longer be classified as unPRed stale work.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"This failure mode is tied to real git history transformations (rebase/squash) and ancestry semantics, which are easiest to expose with actual VCS operations rather than mocked commit graphs.","test_description":"In a real git repo, construct stale branch state, then resolve via rebase and separately via squash merge into main. Re-run production staleness detection after each operation and assert the branch is no longer classified as `stale-no-pr`.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.78,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
